cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SE

This paper deals with privacy-preserving claims issuance and exchange for virtual asset service providers (VASPs), which involves topics such as cryptography, cybersecurity, and data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the intersection of computer science and social issues such as privacy and regulation. The paper also discusses data management and exchange, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), respectively. Finally, the paper proposes a consortium trust network arrangement, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it involves designing and implementing a network of software systems.
